lyrics:
[Verse]
In Palm Springs, there's a diva so rare
Miss Bea Haven with her crazy flair
Enchanting crowds with her spellbinding charms
She's the kooky icon with open arms

[Chorus]
The magic of Miss Bea Haven, oh so grand
Cashton and bling feathers in her hand
Outlandishly colorful wigs, she's a sight
Fun, fun, fun, bringing joy day and night

[Verse 1]
In a desert so vast, under the sun's golden ray
She glides on her scooter, in a kaftan so chic and so gray
With the wind in her hair, and a smile upon her face
She's the desert diva, embracing freedom's embrace

[Chorus]
Kaftans in the desert, flowing with pure grace
She's a vision of confidence, ruling this vast space
With each stride she takes, her spirit soars high
In her kaftan, she conquers, with style that won't die
